H0.text: The technical Hawaiian-English word 'aa', commonly the first two-letter word in a dictionary, refers to. Ahupuaa

H1.text: The technical Hawaiian-English word 'aa', commonly the first two-letter word in a dictionary, refers to. Ama

H2.text: The technical Hawaiian-English word 'aa', commonly the first two-letter word in a dictionary, refers to. Anahola

H3.text: The technical Hawaiian-English word 'aa', commonly the first two-letter word in a dictionary, refers to. Aʻa

A4.text: 'Aʻā is basaltic lava characterized by a rough or rubbly surface composed of broken lava blocks called clinker.

A5.text: The word is Hawaiian meaning 'stony rough lava', but also to 'burn' or 'blaze'.
